South African doctor: Omik Jung has strong transmission power, but most of them are mild
Many doctors and medical experts in South Africa believe that the Omik Jung variant of the coronavirus causes milder symptoms than the Delta variant, although it spreads faster.
According to the Associated Press report, with the spread of the Omik Jung variant in South Africa, more than 5,000 doctors from Gauteng Province in South Africa formed a physicians' organization to report that the COVID-19 patients they are currently treating have relatively mild symptoms, such as physical pain and cough, and other flu-like symptoms.
Dr. Unben Pillay, director of the organization, said he sees dozens of patients every day, but none of them have yet to be hospitalized.
“They were able to control the disease at home, and most people recovered within 10 to 14 days of quarantine,” Pillay said. ”
He said this included elderly patients and those with health problems, who would have been more likely to become seriously ill due to coronavirus infection.
He said that in comparison, in the last wave of the Delta outbreak, the COVID-19 patients he treated “had trouble breathing and low blood oxygen levels.
Many people will be hospitalized within a few days”.
Two weeks after Southern Africa first reported the Omiquillon mutated strain, other doctors shared similar experiences.
While it will take weeks to gather enough data, doctors' observations and early evidence provide some clues.
According to a summary by South Africa's National Institute of Infectious Diseases: Of the COVID-19 patients hospitalized in recent weeks, only 30% were seriously ill, half the severe rate of the previous wave of the epidemic; the average length of hospitalization was shortened from 8 days to 2.8 days; and of the recent COVID-19 patients, only 3% died, and of the early outbreaks in South Africa, the death rate reached 20%.
Willem Hanekom, director of the African Institute of Health, citing data from the National Institute of Infectious Diseases and other reports, said: “Currently, almost all indications indicate that it is a milder disease. ”
He also said, “It's still early days, and we need to get later data.
Normally, hospitalizations and deaths occur late, and we only entered this wave of the epidemic for two weeks. ”
Meanwhile, scientists around the world are observing the number of cases and hospitalizations, while testing the effectiveness of current vaccines and treatments.
Although Delta remains the main COVID-19 strain in the world, Omikjon cases are occurring in dozens of countries, with South Africa at the epicenter of the outbreak.
According to health officials, new cases detected in Gauteng increased by 400% in the first week of December. Tests showed that the Omik Jung variant accounted for more than 90% of cases.
Education Review: What do we rely on to save abducted children?
If we compare the famous public service advertising slogan “No killing without buying or selling”, then in a favorable environment where there is no demand for “abduction”, mass prevention and control and anti-abduction by the whole population make abduction and trafficking unprofitable, risky, and expensive, and such crimes will not occur repeatedly.
Recently, an emergency release platform for information on missing children developed by the Abduction and Abduction Office of the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security went live.
This is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for publishing information on missing children and to recover abducted children in a timely manner.
When I heard that this app was called “Reunion”, I felt very warm.
The new technological means are not only named “literature and art” and are full of feelings, but informatization is also properly used, practical and effective.
The primary goal of law enforcement against abduction is to recover abducted children and protect their personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of the suspect.
The meaning of criminal punishment, from individual punishment, social prevention to legal education, can be cited as many “big words”.
However, before abduction and trafficking cases come to an end, priority should be given to the personal safety of the victims.
Prioritize matters. Under the urgent purpose of “rescue”, topics that are widely divided and controversial, such as “whether child abduction and trafficking should always be the death penalty”, can be put aside and discussed cautiously; however, the rescue of abducted children cannot wait.
Based on their experience in investigating such cases, traffickers are accustomed to stay away from the crime site as soon as they succeed.
If the abduction hunt is delayed for one more minute, the child may be one step further away from the parents, and the difficulty of detecting the case will increase by one point.
Under such circumstances, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with an effective method such as the “Reunion” platform that directly helps to detect cases and recover children.
After all, “abduction” is a major task that needs to be done by operating the entire legal system.
Combating crime and safeguarding the rights and interests of children and parents, from the improvement of legislation to the protection of the judiciary and the meticulous enforcement of the law, there is no need to implement the care of “caring for young children and helping the weak”.
In addition, the prevention of child abduction and trafficking can be done better from families to society.
For example, in a common case, a family of three is resting at a train station, parents are asleep, and only wake up to find that the child is gone.
A two-year-old cannot be expected to have sufficient self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, you should have at least a fair sense of protection.
Both parents taking turns resting or placing the child under secure protection are the minimum means of preventing child abduction.
Looking at the other side of the police's fight against abduction and trafficking crimes, parties that buy abducted children should also receive attention and punishment.
A single illegal act is often just one link in a long chain.
According to the provisions of China's Criminal Law, the statutory penalty for the crime of child abduction and trafficking is 5 years; if the circumstances are particularly serious, the death penalty may be imposed and property confiscation will be imposed.
The sentence is high and the maximum sentence is heavy. Under the general trend of “light punishment”, the crime of child abduction and trafficking is clearly a crime with heavier penalties.
However, there are still quite a few cases of abduction and trafficking that occur every year.
It can be seen that some people are lagging behind in their views on raising children and have little legal awareness.
Legal education for this group of people should be followed up at the same time.
To effectively control the crime of abduction and trafficking, we cannot rely on strict government enforcement alone.
If there is a widespread “market” for abduction, abductors and traffickers are tempted to profit, continue to innovate methods of abduction and trafficking, and form a “fight” situation with law enforcement officials, the anti-abduction operation is bound to fall into an inefficient muddle.
Therefore, breaking down the concept of backwardness and popularizing common sense of the law will also help root out the crime of abduction, trafficking and buying of children.
