Girl used as an arrow target to raise money for her sister: “It's okay to think it's sarcasm” - Xinhua
A girl in Wulin Square in Hangzhou stood in front of a large wooden board with the words “human target, ten yuan, one arrow” written on the board.
Yesterday morning, a photo of “Hangzhou girl willing to be an 'arrow target' to raise money for her sister” blew up the circle of friends.
The photo shows a girl in Wulin Square in Hangzhou standing in front of a large wooden board slightly taller than a person. The words “human target, ten yuan, one arrow” were written on the board, signaling passers-by to use a bow and arrow to shoot after paying.
The act triggered a buzz among netizens.
Last night, the head of propaganda at the Xiacheng Branch of the Hangzhou Municipal Public Security Bureau confirmed to Xinjing News reporters that the police confirmed that the girl made such an aggressive move only to raise money for her sister, but this kind of behavior was not worth promoting. After being warned, the girl had already left the local police station yesterday.
Girl's street “arrow target” fundraising admonished
In the picture circulated online, a long-haired girl stood in front of a large wooden board in the font “one”. The words “human target, ten yuan, one arrow” were written on the board in black ink. Her bank account number, WeChat, Alipay account, etc. were written on the other wooden board in front of her.
The image sparked controversy after it went online.
Some netizens believe that this move is a “begging act of Bo's eyeballs,” and many netizens also expressed sympathy for this.
“We discovered what we discovered when we patrolled the square at around 10:00 a.m. on the 23rd. At that time, there were already quite a few onlookers. ”
Police officers at the Tianshui police station near the scene of the incident said in an interview with local media that there were two girls who set up the stalls, both around the age of 20, and dressed up young and beautiful.
Among them, the girl who works as a “human target” has been crying and begging passers-by to play this game; the other girl is on the side to help sipping, saying that her friend's sister has leukemia and is in urgent need of surgery now, so please help everyone.
“We got in touch with the local police in Guizhou and learned that the girl was fundraising for her sister's leukemia treatment. ”
Last night, the head of publicity at the Xiacheng Branch of the Hangzhou Public Security Bureau told Xinjing News reporters that the girl's name was Ji Jiali and raised donations for her sister Ji Jiayan.
However, since treatment still costs more than 300,000, it was impossible to think of a good way to raise funds for a while, and only then did this act be carried out.
He said that during the whole process, one of the two girls was a target and the other was responsible for laying hands, but they did not participate in it. No one was found shooting arrows during the whole process, but someone watched and took pictures and posted them on Weibo.
Later, the police assessed by the public security department that the bow and arrow used did not fall within the scope of control.
The person in charge said, “This kind of blog eyeball fundraising method is not advocated.”
She had already left the police station after being warned by the police station residents.
