Educational Thoughts: How to Make “School Bullies” and “Learn Slag” Get Their Own Place in College Examinations-Xinhua
Three students from Lanzhou Jiaotong University wrote to university leaders, reflecting their confusion about the university exam, and making demands to make the exam more difficult and change the exam question type so that the exam can truly reflect the students' actual level.
Indeed, university exams have been a “hot topic” for a long time.
On university campuses, students come from all over the world, and their ability levels vary. Coupled with varying degrees of study, the study conditions vary greatly.
It is inevitable that there are different feelings when assessing groups with such diverse characteristics.
Of course, if the exam question type is single and the repetition rate is high, and the questions are too simple, it will inevitably cause another very different feeling.
Students who do not have any merit may be able to pass the exam by concentrating on surprise attacks before the exam. If they think about other methods, they may achieve the effect of doing more with less.
As a result, there is a “strange status quo” where “learning slag” can usually pass the level without investing, and even get a high score; “school bullies” usually never drop out of class, their homework and notes are good, and exams are not much higher.
In this way, students at Lanzhou Jiaotong University reported that the problems that exist in university examinations are not without cause, and I believe this situation does not only exist at Lanzhou Jiaotong University.
In this sense, I would like to praise these 3 students who wrote straight letters.
In fact, everyone who has attended university knows that it is not uncommon to surprise exam preparation, find various ways to “extract” exam questions from teachers, try to draw the scope of the exam, and get “key counseling” before the exam. It is not unusual to even include a small copy in the exam and ask the teacher to exalt himself after the exam.
In the author's view, as a teaching quality assessment guide, measuring whether or not a university exam passes or fails depends more on teachers' comprehensive grasp of teaching and learning, and scientific propositions based on this.
Entering the undergraduate level, majors begin to be subdivided, and many major courses focus on basic knowledge.
Needless to say, whether you have a comprehensive grasp of the basic knowledge points of a subject is the content to be examined in the university exam.
Undergraduate knowledge is basically the basic theory of the subject and basic common sense. From the point of view of knowledge, there is not much room for change, and it is basically fixed.
As one teacher said, “I studied the basic knowledge of mathematics at university 20 years ago, and I'm still studying it now, which is still the focus. ”
However, the knowledge points are basically the same, which does not mean that the exam question type is single or the test questions are repeated.
In many universities, examination groups are generally formed, and examination papers are co-ordinated by senior teachers of the subject. Examination papers are also read with the participation of all teachers in charge of the subject, so that repetition of test questions can be overcome to a certain extent.
However, it is necessary to draw up a set of test questions that conform to the reality of teaching and learning. According to the overall situation of students' learning, the questions are easily distributed normally. It is also necessary to comprehensively grasp the teaching situation and comprehensively analyze the students' degree of learning, so that the exam propositions have a dynamic grasp of the difficulty and question type, which can not only highlight the basic knowledge examination, but also take into account the ability test, and innovate the question type.
The exam is the baton of university education. If there is any kind of exam, students will have a corresponding exam preparation plan. In the long run, it will affect the effectiveness of university education.
The Lanzhou Jiaotong University campus attaches great importance to the students' proposal letters and has deployed a rectification plan throughout the school.
All teaching units are required to organize teachers to conduct discussions and comparative self-checks on course closing examinations, formulate exam paper propositions and related systems. At the same time, they strengthen supervision and inspection of exam paper propositions and review links, refine the evaluation of results, and strengthen the comprehensive assessment of all aspects of curriculum teaching.
Mechanically solving the problems of single test question type, repeated topics and other issues that university examinations need to face. Of course, a corresponding system needs to be introduced, but kung fu is expensive on a daily basis, requires teachers to have a comprehensive grasp of the teaching situation, not only the teaching content, but also the students' learning situation, both ends thoroughly, teaching and learning will be better connected, forming a virtuous interaction, the exam will also be more in line with reality, so that the “school bully” and “Learn slag” Each has its own place.
