Negative nucleic acid for 48 hours, set up a “buffer zone” The joint prevention and control mechanism of the State Council issued a document calling for strengthening epidemic prevention and control in port cities-Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency report of December 11 from Beijing (by staff reporters Dong Ruifeng and Gu Tiancheng) - The joint prevention and control mechanism of the State Council recently issued a notice on strengthening the prevention and control of COVID-19 in port cities, requiring people who have recently left land border port cities (except those connected to ports in Hong Kong and Macao) to have a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours.
According to the notice, the time frame for the above requirements is from the date when each province, region and city determines the port city scope and announces it, until March 15, 2022.
In addition, the notice also proposes that port cities that are in a position to do so can study setting up buffer zones for epidemic prevention and control in their jurisdictions.
Relevant officials from the Bureau of Disease Prevention and Control of the National Health Commission explained that for some port cities, cross-border border trade is the main economic pillar of the region, and border people from both sides have frequent exchanges.
The implementation of a zoning differentiated management policy, changing from one line of defense for spillover prevention and control to two lines of defense, is expected to move the gate forward, reduce the risk of epidemic spillover, and achieve the maximum effectiveness of epidemic prevention and control with minimal social impact and minimum social cost.
Recently, there have been many local cluster outbreaks in China, all imported from abroad through port cities.
The above notice points out that this revealed problems such as untimely epidemic monitoring and early warning in some places, non-implementation of closed-loop management of personnel in high-risk positions, formality of regular nucleic acid testing, inadequate killing of cold chain items in all aspects, irregular management of centralized isolation sites, and insufficient scientific and accurate emergency response to the epidemic.
The notice requires that efforts be made in nine areas, including improving the epidemic prevention and control mechanisms in port cities, improving the epidemic monitoring and early warning system, and implementing border control measures, to accelerate the completion of shortcomings in prevention and control in port cities, do a good job of prevention and control without relaxation, scientifically and accurately, and tighten the foreign defense import defense line.
The notice emphasizes that all port cities should simultaneously study and deploy epidemic prevention and control and livelihood security work, publish and unblock livelihood security hotlines, regularly investigate emerging hidden dangers in the supply and price of basic living materials, etc., and promptly resolve and proactively respond to outstanding problems reflected by the masses.
According to the notice, the port cities referred to in it include the county (city, district, flag), city (prefecture, state, league) and municipality directly under the Central Government where open land, waterway and air ports are located. The specific scope shall be determined by each province (autonomous region or municipality directly under the Central Government) according to the needs of epidemic prevention and control and announced in a timely manner.
