There's an appointment in the starry sky丨The Gemini meteor shower ushered in a big way on the
Xinhua News Agency report of December 12 from Tianjin (by staff reporter Zhou Runjian) - Astronomical science experts explained that as the last large-scale meteor shower of the year, the Gemini meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere, will be extremely large on December 14. Friends who like meteor showers can observe it in the middle of the night after that day.
Beijing astronomy enthusiast Anjiu filmed the Gemini meteor shower in Qinghai on December 13, 2018.
The parent body of most meteor showers is a periodic comet, but the parent object of the Gemini meteor shower is the 3200 asteroid Faetong, which is an Apollo asteroid.
The Gemini meteor shower is also the second meteor shower currently known not to be “bred” by a comet.
Xiu Lipeng, director of the Tianjin Astronomical Society and an astronomical science expert, explained that just like Lunar New Year blockbusters, Gemini meteor showers generally appear at the end of the year, and the “release schedule” can last from December 4 to 17.
The meteor shower is known for its high flow and stability. Together with the quadrant meteor shower and the Perseid meteor shower, it is called the top three meteor showers in the northern hemisphere.
A distinctive feature of the Gemini meteor shower is that the meteor body is slow, colorful, and there are many fire meteors. It is suitable for both visual and astronomy beginners to shoot.
Tianjin astronomy enthusiast Yang Jing filmed the Gemini meteor shower in Jizhou, Tianjin on December 13, 2020.
Astronomical forecasts show that this year's Gemini meteor shower will be extremely large at around 15:00 on December 14. The maximum ZHR (the number of meteors that can be seen per hour when the radiation point is directly above the overhead under ideal observation conditions) is 150.
Gemini meteor shower recommendation index chart.
“Last year, people were deeply impressed by the 'colorful setting' Gemini meteor shower, but this year's Gemini meteor shower will be disturbed by moonlight, and the degree of excitement will be slightly discounted.
The 14th is November 11 of the lunar calendar. The moon phase is a bulging moon. The bright moonlight will interfere with observations. Fortunately, the moon will fall in the middle of the night. At this time, the radiation point of the Gemini meteor shower will also rise relatively high.
Friends who like meteor showers can observe these hours after the moon sets in the middle of the night, but be careful to keep warm from the cold. ”
How can we observe as many meteors as possible?
“It is not recommended to observe in a city. You can choose a place in the suburbs or countryside with a high altitude, low light pollution, and a wide view facing the northeast, and then wait patiently until the moon sets to observe visually.
It should be noted that the Gemini meteor shower has a lot of flow in all directions, so you don't need to keep an eye on the radiation point of the Gemini meteor shower when observing it.
If you want to shoot a gorgeous 'meteor shower blockbuster film', it's best to choose a wide-angle, large-aperture lens, and use a high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting.
Tripods, battery backup, and shutter cables are also essential for stability and continuity. ”
Xiu Lipeng cautioned.
